comments: Okafor (NOP) establishes himself in a legal screening position in Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and is firming up when the contact occurs during the pick.
Adams (OKC) makes contact with the ball during Holiday's (NOP) driving shot attempt.
Holiday (NOP) briefly places a hand/arm to Paul's (OKC) front during the drive but the contact is marginal.
Holiday (NOP) establishes himself in a legal screening position in Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and is firming up when the contact occurs during the screen.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) makes incidental contact to Redick's (NOP) arm after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Adams (OKC) establishes himself in a legal screening position in Redick's (NOP) path and is firming up when the contact occurs during the pick.
Okafor (NOP) slightly extends his forearm into Adams' (OKC) front but the contact does not affect his ability to get to the rebound.

Paul (OKC) rests his left hand on Ingram's (NOP) body but he quickly removes it as Ingram begins his upward shooting motion without affecting his trajectory on the jump shot attempt. The reach-in from Paul's right hand does not make contact with Ingram's body.
Ingram (NOP) maintains a legal guarding position on Paul (OKC) as the two players come together and engage.
Holiday (NOP) reaches in and makes marginal contact to Schroder's (OKC) arm that does not affect his ability to maintain control of the ball during his dribble.

During the inbound, Paul (OKC) briefly places a hand on the opposite side of Ingram's (NOP) body as both players move in the same direction. Paul slides that hand off and the marginal contact does not affect Ingram's ability to get to the inbound pass.
Ferguson (OKC) reaches out and briefly grasps Redick's (NOP) jersey as he moves around the screen. The contact is deemed marginal.
Okafor (NOP) is in a wide stance when he initiates leg to leg contact to Ferguson (OKC) during the screen.
Holiday (NOP) and Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) arrive at the ball simultaneously during the rebound and both players engage in marginal contact prior to separating.
